{
  "texts": [
    "Particularly in its self-attention version, it facilitates processing relevant elements within a sequence transition from one layer to another, correlating them with each other and providing context in a vectorial manner.",
    "Moreover, it achieves computational efficiency compared to recurrent layers, especially in domains where sequence length is more critical than dimensionality, such as linguistic strings.",
    "Consequently, this statistical contextualization, based on extensive training datasets and ongoing refinements, yields a semantic capacity or impression thereof, encompassing syntactic processing treated similarly in terms of vector representations (words and word contexts).",
    "Without delving too deeply into further technical aspects, this mechanism enables the assignment of different vector representations to the same word based on its context.",
    "A series of scores is assigned to the elements of the word sequence (the sentence in question), indicating the probability that words in the sentence are more or less relevant."
  ]
}